---
name: new-spec
description: Create a new spec (spec.md + plan.md + tasks.md) for a given feature.
---

Configuration:
- FEATURE_NAME: my-feature

Objective: Create a complete spec for {FEATURE_NAME} following SDD methodology.

Mandatory reading order:
1. .github/copilot-instructions.md
2. .specify/memory/constitution.md
3. All existing specs in .specify/specs/

Execution flow:
1. Count existing folders in .specify/specs/ to get the next number.
2. Create .specify/specs/<NNN>-<slug>/
3. Create spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md inside.

spec.md: status, dependencies, context, objective, normative reference, acceptance criteria, out of scope.
plan.md: architecture, module responsibilities, technical decisions, no normative duplication.
tasks.md: checkbox list (- [ ]), atomic tasks mapping 1:1 to criteria.

Required output:
1. Spec folder and files created.
2. Acceptance criteria summary.
3. Task count.
4. Open questions (if any).
